From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [Q3.6-14] Remove rfind/find — minja renders no position method

Targets: templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja (shipped default stack:
Q3.6-1 + Q3.6-2 + Q3.6-3 + Q3.6-4 + Q3.6-5 + Q3.6-6 + Q3.6-12)

Status: ACTIVE — part of the shipped default stack.

Failure mode (CRITICAL, and invisible to a jinja2-only harness): minja, the
C++ Jinja engine in llama.cpp / LM Studio's GGUF path, implements NO
position-returning string method. `rfind`, `find` and `index` are all
Undefined, and calling one aborts the whole render:

    Error: Callee is not a function: got Undefined (hint: 'rfind')
    (llama.cpp build 9290 / bcfd1989e, `llama-template-analysis`)

Both Q3.6-3 (auto-close unclosed `<think>`) and Q3.6-5 (thinking sentinels)
were written with `rfind`/`find`, so the SHIPPED template could not render at
all on llama.cpp. `llama-template-analysis` reported `supports_tools: false`
for it, because minja bailed before reaching the tools branch. After this
patch the same tool reports `supports_tools: true`, `supports_tool_calls:
true`, `supports_parallel_tool_calls: true`.

This is the same engine-divergence class as P4 (`| safe`) and the Q3.6-5
`.replace()` index-0 hardening: jinja2 accepts the construct, so the repo's
render harness cannot see the breakage. It was found by running the template
through minja directly, and `tests/test_render.py::test_minja_*` now gates
every shipped and opt-in template on a real minja parse so it cannot recur.

Fix — two position-free reformulations, both using only operations minja
implements (`split`, `join`, `last`, slicing, `length`, `in`):

1. **Q3.6-5 rightmost-wins sentinel.** Whichever sentinel occurs LAST leaves
   the SHORTER trailing segment, because the other sentinel's trailing
   segment must still contain it. Equality is impossible while both are
   present, so the comparison is total:

       (merged_system.split('<|think_off|>')|last|length)
         < (merged_system.split('<|think_on|>')|last|length)

2. **Q3.6-3 auto-close.** `_tail` is everything after the LAST `<think>`; the
   block is unclosed iff no closer (`</think>` or `</thinking>`) appears in
   `_tail`. The injection point is the FIRST `<tool_call>` inside `_tail` —
   exactly the "at or after the last `<think>`" tool call the old
   `content.find('<tool_call>', last_think)` searched for, so the
   earlier-completed-tool-call case Q3.6-3 was hardened against still
   behaves correctly. Reconstruction is
   `_head + '<think>' + _pre + '</think>' + '<tool_call>' + _post`, which is
   byte-for-byte what the old slice form produced.

Behaviour: **byte-identical under jinja2** — verified across 120 render
combos (every qwen3.6 fixture including the Q3.6-8 eval cases x
{default, tools, preserve_thinking on/off, enable_thinking=false}, six
adversarial auto-close shapes, and eleven sentinel arrangements including
both conflict orders, doubled sentinels and index-0 placement). The existing
Q3.6-3 and Q3.6-5 regression tests pass unchanged.

Diffs against the Q3.6-12-applied state.

